    {"id": 4, "question": "What does the passage say about online returns compared to in-store returns?", "options": ["A) Online returns are less common than in-store returns", "B) Online shoppers make returns far more frequently than in-store shoppers", "C) Returns have no significant environmental impact", "D) Retailers have solved the returns problem through improved sizing technology"], "answer": "B", "explanation": "Online shoppers make returns far more frequently than in-store shoppers, generating additional transportation emissions and waste."},
    {"id": 5, "question": "What concern does the passage raise about gig economy delivery workers?", "options": ["A) They earn too much compared to traditional retail workers", "B) There are not enough of them to meet demand", "C) They often face insecure employment, low pay, and minimal legal protections", "D) They contribute significantly to traffic congestion in cities"], "answer": "C", "explanation": "Gig economy delivery workers often face insecure employment, low pay, and minimal legal protections."}
